# Pixie .cursorrules

## 🎯 Product Identity

**What Pixie is:** A marketer-first SaaS platform for managing website tracking.
**Who uses it:** Marketers, not engineers. Assume zero technical knowledge.
**Design vibe:** Warm professional — think Vercel, Linear, or Notion. Clean, confident, modern. Not a developer tool.

---

## 🎨 Visual Identity

**Mode:** Dark mode only. Force `class="dark"` on `<html>`.
**Tone:** Refined and trustworthy. No cyber aesthetics, no neon overload, no sci-fi jargon.

---

## 🖍️ Color Palette

| Role | Token | Notes |
|------|-------|-------|
| Page background | `bg-slate-950` | The base — used everywhere |
| Card surface | `bg-slate-900` | Solid, not transparent |
| Card border | `border-slate-800` | Subtle dividers |
| Primary accent | `bg-violet-600` | Buttons, active states — use sparingly |
| Primary hover | `bg-violet-500` | Hover state for violet elements |
| Success / Live | `emerald-500` / `emerald-400` | Active status only |
| Warning / Setup | `amber-400` / `amber-500` | Pending/incomplete state |
| Error | `rose-500` / `rose-400` | Destructive actions, error states |
| Text default | `text-slate-200` | Body text |
| Text headings | `text-white` | Page titles, card headings |
| Text muted | `text-slate-400` / `text-slate-500` | Descriptions, hints, labels |
| Code / monospace | `text-violet-300` on `bg-slate-950` | Script tags, IDs |

**Do not use:** `fuchsia`, `neon` glow stacks on body text or decorative backgrounds, `bg-slate-900/40 backdrop-blur-md` for standard cards (use solid `.card-solid` instead).

---

## 🔠 Typography

- **Headings:** Inter — use `font-bold` or `font-semibold`, negative letter spacing (`-0.025em`)
- **Body:** Inter — `text-sm` for most UI, `text-xs` for hints and labels
- **Code / IDs:** JetBrains Mono — only for actual code, script tags, and pixel IDs
- **Page titles:** `text-xl font-bold text-white` — not gradient text, not 4xl
- **Section headings:** `text-sm font-semibold text-white`
- **Gradient text** (`.gradient-text`): Reserved for the Pixie logo / hero moments only — not every heading

---

## 🧩 UI Component Rules

### Cards
Use `.card-solid` for all standard cards:
```
bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 rounded-xl
```
Use `.glass-card` only for modals and overlays:
```
bg-slate-900/60 backdrop-blur-sm border border-slate-800 rounded-xl
```
Never stack multiple blur/transparency effects.

### Buttons
- **Primary (NeonButton):** `bg-violet-600 hover:bg-violet-500 text-white` — subtle shadow only, no large glow
- **Secondary:** `bg-slate-800 hover:bg-slate-700 text-slate-200 border border-slate-700`
- **Ghost:** `text-slate-400 hover:text-slate-200 hover:bg-slate-800/60`
- **Destructive:** `text-slate-400 hover:text-rose-400 hover:bg-rose-500/10`
- Button heights: `h-9` for standard, `h-10` for prominent actions

### Input Fields
```
bg-slate-800 border-slate-700 text-white placeholder:text-slate-500
focus:border-violet-500 focus:ring-1 focus:ring-violet-500/30
```

### Status Badges (use `<StatusBadge>` component)
- `active` → displays **"Live"** — `emerald-500` dot (animated pulse), `emerald-400` text
- `pending` → displays **"Setup Required"** — `amber-400` dot, `amber-400` text
- `paused` → displays **"Paused"** — `slate-500` dot, `slate-400` text
- Never show raw status strings (`"active"`, `"pending"`, `"paused"`) directly in the UI

### Sidebar
- Width: `w-56`
- Background: `bg-slate-950`
- Border: `border-r border-slate-800`
- Active nav item: `bg-violet-600/15 text-violet-300 border border-violet-500/20`
- Inactive nav item: `text-slate-400 hover:text-slate-200 hover:bg-slate-800/60`
- No vertical bar glow indicators — use background highlight instead

### Modals
Use the `GlassModal` component. Inner card uses `.glass-card p-6`.

### Tabs
Use the `Tabs` component from `@/components/ui/tabs`.
Tab names must be plain English — no technical terms.
- Correct: "Overview", "Analytics IDs", "Conversions"
- Wrong: "Configuration", "Rules", "Pixel IDs"

---

## 🗣️ Language Rules (Marketer-First)

This is the most important section. Every word in the UI must be readable by a marketer with no technical background.

### Status labels
| Internal value | UI label |
|---------------|---------|
| `active` | Live |
| `pending` | Setup Required |
| `paused` | Paused |

### Navigation labels
| Internal name | UI label |
|--------------|---------|
| Dashboard | My Sites |
| Settings | Settings |
| Documentation | Help & Setup Guide |

### Feature labels
| Technical term | Plain English |
|---------------|--------------|
| Pixel IDs | Analytics IDs / Connect your analytics |
| GA4 Measurement ID | Google Analytics 4 ID |
| Meta Pixel ID | Facebook / Meta Pixel ID |
| Event rules | Conversion events |
| Selector | (Hidden — shown only in collapsible "Technical details") |
| Site ID | (Hidden — only shown in the script tag section) |
| pixie.js | (Never shown to the user — it's just "the tracking script") |

### Copy guidelines
- Use "your website" not "site" where possible
- Use "conversion" not "event" in user-facing text
- Use "Turn tracking on/off" not "toggle status"
- Use "Ask your developer to paste this code" not just "Install"
- Use "Google Analytics" not "GA4" in labels
- Use "Facebook / Meta" not "Meta" alone (more recognisable)
- Error messages must be plain sentences: "Incorrect email or password" not Firebase error codes
- Empty states must explain the benefit, not just describe the absence: "Add your first website to start tracking conversions automatically" not "No sites"

---

## 📐 Layout & Spacing

- Max content width: `max-w-3xl` or `max-w-4xl` with `mx-auto`
- Page padding: `px-4 sm:px-6 py-8 lg:py-10`
- Card internal padding: `p-5` standard, `p-6` for forms
- Gap between cards: `space-y-4` or `gap-3`/`gap-4` in grids
- Section headings inside cards: `text-sm font-semibold text-white mb-1` + `text-xs text-slate-400` description below

---

## 📱 Responsive Design

- **Mobile:** Top navigation bar with Pixie logo + hamburger → slide-out sidebar overlay
- **Tablet:** Same as mobile until `lg` breakpoint
- **Desktop (lg+):** Persistent left sidebar `w-56`, content fills remaining width
- Cards: `sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3` for site lists
- Never rely on hover-only interactions for mobile critical actions
- All modals: full-width on mobile, capped width (`max-w-md`) on desktop

---

## 🚫 Anti-Patterns (Never Do These)

- No cyber grid background patterns (`bg-[linear-gradient(...)]` decorative grids)
- No ambient glow orb decorations (`absolute ... bg-violet-500/30 blur-[128px]`)
- No fake data in charts or sparklines — if there's no real data, don't show the chart
- No raw Firebase error messages exposed to users
- No CSS selectors, IDs, or technical strings visible without a "Technical details" toggle
- No "Command Center" or similar dev-tool language
- No `backdrop-blur-md` on standard page cards (only modals/overlays)
- No gradient text on anything other than the logo/hero
- No `debug=true` in script tags shown to users
- No stacking of multiple box-shadow glow effects
- No heavy use of `animate-pulse` on decorative elements

---

## 🎭 Interactions & Animation

- **Transitions:** `transition-colors duration-150` for colour changes, `transition-all duration-150` for layout changes
- **Hover on cards:** `hover:border-slate-700 hover:bg-slate-800/60` — subtle, no glow
- **Page entry:** `.animate-fade-in` (`opacity 0→1` + `translateY 4px→0`)
- **Loading states:** Single minimal spinner (`h-5 w-5 border-2 border-violet-500 border-t-transparent animate-spin`)
- **Success feedback:** `sonner` toast — `toast.success("Descriptive message")` — no full-screen celebrations
- **Status dot on Live badge:** `pulse-slow` animation only — nowhere else

---

## ⚡ New User Onboarding

When a site has `status === "pending"`, always show a **Setup Checklist** with three steps:
1. Connect an analytics platform (GA4 or Meta Pixel ID)
2. Install the tracking script
3. Track your first conversion

Each step uses `CheckCircle2` (done) or `Circle` (not done) icons from Lucide. Mark steps complete dynamically based on actual data.

---

## 🛡️ Engineering Standards

### TypeScript
- Never use `any`. Always define interfaces for props and data shapes.
- Interface names: PascalCase (`SiteData`, `EventRule`)
- Props interfaces: ComponentName + Props (`PixelConfigFormProps`)

### React
- Functional components only: `const Component = () => {}`
- Use `useCallback` / `useMemo` for expensive calculations or prop-passed functions
- UI components (`/components/ui`): purely presentational
- Feature components (`/components/dashboard`): contain state and logic
- Page files (`page.tsx`): fetch data and compose feature components only

### Firebase
- Never import `firebase-admin` in client-side files
- Use `onSnapshot` for all dashboard data (real-time updates)
- Wrap all Firebase calls in `try/catch`
- Show user-friendly error messages via `sonner` (`toast.error`)
- Never expose raw Firebase error codes in the UI

### Firestore field naming
- `status`: `"active"` | `"pending"` | `"paused"`
- `owner_id`: user UID
- `trackingConfig.pixels.ga4`: GA4 Measurement ID
- `trackingConfig.pixels.meta`: Meta Pixel ID
- `trackingConfig.events[]`: array of event rules
- `suggested_events[]`: AI-scanned conversion point suggestions

---

## 📂 File Structure

```
dashboard/
  app/
    page.tsx                      # Loading redirect only
    login/page.tsx                # Auth page
    dashboard/page.tsx            # Site list
    dashboard/[siteId]/page.tsx   # Site detail
    dashboard/settings/page.tsx   # Account settings
    dashboard/docs/page.tsx       # Help guide
  components/
    ui/                           # Presentational primitives
    layouts/sidebar-layout.tsx    # App shell
    auth/auth-guard.tsx           # Route protection
    providers/firebase-provider.tsx
    dashboard/                    # Feature components
      add-site-modal.tsx
      pixel-config-form.tsx
      event-rules-list.tsx
      suggested-rules-list.tsx
  lib/
    firebase.ts                   # SDK initialisation
    utils.ts                      # cn() helper
```

---

## 🤖 Cursor Behaviour

- Write code first, explain only if asked
- Never add decorative comments like `// 🚀 Handling auth`
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` whenever accepting `className` props
- Always use `sonner` (`toast.success` / `toast.error`) for feedback — never `alert()`
- Before writing a delete or destructive action, add a confirmation step or comment `// TODO: confirm before delete`
- Keep page components thin — move logic into feature components

---

**The north star: every screen should feel like it was built by a thoughtful design team at a modern SaaS company. A marketer should be able to use Pixie on day one with zero explanation.**
